{
  "high_level_description": "A vertically oriented mixed-media abstract portrait illustration of a young woman in left-facing profile, head bowed, emerging from cool dark pigment on the left into radiant magenta, coral, orange, and gold bursts on the right across a heavily weathered canvas.",
  "compositional_deconstruction": {
    "background": "Heavily weathered mixed-media canvas filling the elongated 9:16 frame edge to edge. The left half is dominated by a cool field of graphite gray, muted dusty blue, and smoky black pigment layered like aged plaster with visible accumulations along rough uneven edges. The right half ignites with saturated magenta, coral pink, warm orange, and golden yellow pigments bleeding outward in soft cloud-like washes. Thin scratches, hairline cracks, and faint stains weave horizontally and diagonally across the entire composition. Encaustic and mixed-media texture throughout — visible brush drag, scraped passages, translucent glazes over opaque underlayers, fine craquelure cracking across darker regions. Full-bleed contemporary fine-art painterly treatment with no hard digital edges.",
    "elements": [
      {
        "type": "obj",
        "desc": "Young woman in left-facing profile anchored at the vertical center of the canvas, occupying roughly the central two-thirds of the frame as the focal subject. Head gently bowed, features soft and partially obscured, rendered in deep blue-black tones that bleed into the surrounding surface. Her skin and silhouette dissolve at the edges into the cool dark pigment field on the left and the luminous color burst on the right."
      },
      {
        "type": "obj",
        "desc": "Wisps of hair trailing downward from the crown and nape of the figure, dissolving into translucent paint layers and shadow along the lower half of the figure. Dark strands fade into the cool grays below and catch fragments of warm pigment where they cross the right-side color burst."
      },
